text: Consider a function that takes as parameters in this order: two char's a and b; a 48 byte struct c; five int's d, e, f, g, and h; and a 128-bit struct i? (Note: When stored on the stack on the y86, any value that takes up less than 8 bytes will be aligned to 8 bytes, e.g., a char on the stack will use 8 bytes of space.) How many bytes of stack space will the parameters take up? integer @ InvalidA
